A library that creates a connection b/w MongoDB and the Node.js
It is the ODM library (Object Document library)



A JavaScript object modeling tool: Mongoose is a 
popular library used in Node.js applications that 
provides a straightforward way to interact with
 MongoDB databases. It helps in defining data 
 structures (schemas), validating data, and performing
  CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations on
MongoDB collections.


Mongoose uses Operation Buffering